item.title: [HBASE-15337] Document date tiered compaction in the book
item.description: We have two new compaction algorithms FIFO and Date tiered that are for time series data. We should document how to use them in the book.
item.summary: Document date tiered compaction in the book

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment: Enis Soztutar - any thoughts if this would get in for 1.3? I.e. ideally this / next week?
Clara Xiong / Duo Zhang do you want to handle this. If not I can take a stab at it.

No, I have to finish HBASE-15454 first so do not have time to do the documentation work here...

Thanks Enis Soztutar.
I can give it a try over the weekend. Thank you Enis Soztutar

I followed the instruction on the Reference book to use mvn clean site -DskipTests but it would not build on my box. Even the master branch won't build. So I am not sure how it looks. I modeled after the documentation for Stripe Compaction. Enis Soztutar Please review.
